The paper introduces a novel supervised training scheme for attention-based classification problems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of subnetworks and competition in this framework, which are common topics in the subfield of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
